{
  "doc_id": "34603",
  "text": "While unconditional image synthesis is an important research area, many practical applications require the model to be conditioned on some prior information. This prior information has many forms, for instance a distorted image for inpainting [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] ; natural image for super-resolution [CITATION_3] or style transfer [CITATION_4] - [CITATION_5] ; text codes for text to image translation [CITATION_6] , [CITATION_7] . In this work, we are particularly interested in classconditioned image generation, as the aim of this work is to investigate how a model learns the representations of the styles, genres, and artists from the artworks.",
